I meet a problem with using the Ninject WCF extension. The service InstanceContextMode is set to PerCall, but it is instantiated for the first time on ServiceHost creation anyway (and afterwards on every client request as expected). When using the standard ServiceHost, the service will only created on client request and not on ServiceHost creation.

It seems, that the problematic part is the contructor of NinjectAbstractServiceHost<T>, where an instance of T (the service) is required, regardless if the service should be a singleton or not. 

    protected NinjectAbstractServiceHost(IServiceBehavior serviceBehavior, T instance, Uri[] baseAddresses)
        : base(serviceBehavior)
    {
        var addresses = new UriSchemeKeyedCollection(baseAddresses);
    
        if (ServiceTypeHelper.IsSingletonService(instance))
        {
            this.InitializeDescription(instance, addresses);
        }
        else
        {
            this.InitializeDescription(typeof(T), addresses);
        }
    } 

Because i defined a PerCall InstanceContextMode a service instantiation without a client request is not expected. 

